-- Swedish Stability Council to look at more measures to strengthen system
-- By Stockholm Newsroom
-- Fri May 23, 2014 07:33AM EDT
-- None



STOCKHOLM, May 23 (Reuters) - A council of top policy authorities in Sweden said on Friday it would look at more measures to strengthen financial stability with a focus on banks' foreign currency financing and household debts.

"In its continued work the council will analyst financial imbalances and possible risks to financial stability," the Financial Stability Council, which consists of the government, central bank, Debt Office and Financial Supervisory Authority said in a statement. "In the light of that, the council will discuss the need for measures and their effects."